\n3\n00:01:26,063 --> 00:01:28,104\nNo, listen,\nI get about a hundred customers a night\n\n4\n00:01:28,438 --> 00:01:29,688\nI can''t keep track of them all.\n\n5\n00:01:29,896 --> 00:01:31,646\nDo you know...\nwell tell me what he likes to eat\n\n6\n00:01:31,979 --> 00:01:32,979\nCause I remember people by what they order\n\n7\n00:01:33,313 --> 00:01:35,104\nNot by their names\n\n8\n00:01:35,813 --> 00:01:37,021\n"Meat Loaf?"\n\n9\n00:01:37,229 --> 00:01:41,521\nWell, I know a Meat Loaf with Mashed\nPotatoes. I know Meat Loaf who likes\n\n10\n00:01:41,729 --> 00:01:45,396\nWell, with Cheese Fries,\nPouched Egg, Onion Rings\n\n11\n00:01:45,854 --> 00:01:47,854\nWhat? He doesn''t like potatoes?\n\n12\n00:01:48,063 --> 00:01:51,438\nWhy don''t you, well,\nyeah give me your number\n\n13\n00:01:51,688 --> 00:01:53,313\nAnd if I see him, I''ll tell him to call you\n\n14\n00:01:53,813 --> 00:01:56,146\nYeah, I promise. I will. OK bye\n\n15\n00:01:59,688 --> 00:02:01,563\nHe''s 5''11" with dark brown hair\n\n16\n00:02:01,771 --> 00:02:04,354\nSorry, I can''t think of any Meat Loafs\nwith Cheese Fries\n\n17\n00:02:04,563 --> 00:02:06,229\nor Onion Rings or Pouched Eggs\n\n18\n00:02:06,521 --> 00:02:08,729\nOr Fried Fillet of Fish\nthat match that description\n\n19\n00:02:09,188 --> 00:02:11,229\nLast time we were here,\nI think he had the pork chops\n\n20\n00:02:11,646 --> 00:02:12,604\nOh why didn''t you say so?\n\n21\n00:02:12,979 --> 00:02:15,438\nThat''s because we supposedly\nhave the best pork chops in the city\n\n22\n00:02:15,646 --> 00:02:16,229\nYou ever tried them?\n\n23\n00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:17,229\nNo, I haven''t\n\n24\n00:02:17,438 --> 00:02:19,271\nWhy not?\nWhat, are you religious or something?\n\n25\n00:02:20,271 --> 00:02:22,146\nListen, have you seen him or not?\n\n26\n00:02:23,521 --> 00:02:27,188\n5''11". Dark brown hair. Pork chops\n\n27\n00:02:27,938 --> 00:02:30,354\nI have actually.\nHe came in here for dinner last night\n\n28\n00:02:30,729 --> 00:02:31,521\nHe ordered two pork chops\n\n29\n00:02:31,771 --> 00:02:34,271\nOne with mashed potatoes and\none with string beans.\n\n30\n00:02:35,313 --> 00:02:36,479\nI guess he was hungry\n\n31\n00:02:36,729 --> 00:02:38,104\nNo, he didn''t eat both of them.\n\n32\n00:02:38,354 --> 00:02:40,271\nOur portions are too big\nfor a person to eat two\n\n33\n00:02:40,604 --> 00:02:42,688\nNo, one was for him and one was\nfor his girlfriend\n\n34\n00:02:43,646 --> 00:02:45,313\nLook! Just get to the point...\n\n35\n00:02:45,646 --> 00:02:47,313\nDon''t-- Don''t change the subject!\n\n36\n00:02:48,979 --> 00:02:50,854\nAre you seeing someone else?\n\n37\n00:02:52,188 --> 00:02:53,146\nWho is she?\n\n38\n00:02:56,354 --> 00:02:57,854\nI hope you both drop dead!\n\n39\n00:03:18,354 --> 00:03:20,146\nIf someone comes in here looking for me\n\n40\n00:03:20,354 --> 00:03:21,521\ngive him these keys\n\n41\n00:03:22,229 --> 00:03:22,979\nWhat do I tell him?\n\n42\n00:03:23,229 --> 00:03:24,479\nTell him he''s an asshole!\n\n43\n00:03:29,771 --> 00:03:30,854\nTaxi!\n\n44\n00:03:54,646 --> 00:03:56,188\nHey, did he pick up the keys?\n\n45\n00:03:56,938 --> 00:03:58,188\nNo, not yet\n\n46\n00:04:09,313 --> 00:04:10,729\nDo you have an extra cigarette?\n\n47\n00:04:10,896 --> 00:04:11,854\nSure\n\n48\n00:04:14,104 --> 00:04:15,313\nRolled it myself\n\n49\n00:04:15,563 --> 00:04:16,438\nThanks\n\n50\n00:04:26,521 --> 00:04:27,563\nYou okay?\n\n51\n00:04:28,229 --> 00:04:29,104\nYeah\n\n52\n00:04:30,688 --> 00:04:32,479\nI haven''t had one in a while\n\n53\n00:04:32,688 --> 00:04:34,354\nI only smoke when I get stressed out\n\n54\n00:04:34,563 --> 00:04:35,438\nWell, you shouldn''t worry so much\n\n55\n00:04:35,854 --> 00:04:37,271\nThat way you''ll avoid lung cancer\n\n56\n00:04:40,854 --> 00:04:42,104\nDo you think she''s pretty?\n\n57\n00:04:43,229 --> 00:04:43,854\nWho?\n\n58\n00:04:44,063 --> 00:04:45,354\nThe girl he was in here with\n\n59\n00:04:46,854 --> 00:04:49,604\nOh, she was okay I guess... I mean\n\n60\n00:04:49,854 --> 00:04:52,188\nNot the type I would prefer\nto have my pork chops with\n\n61\n00:04:52,479 --> 00:04:55,354\nbut "each man to his own", right?\n\n62\n00:04:56,271 --> 00:04:57,604\nYeah right\n\n63\n00:05:35,354 --> 00:05:36,229\nHello\n\n64\n00:05:36,479 --> 00:05:37,479\nHey\n\n65\n00:05:45,063 --> 00:05:46,688\nI need someone to talk to\n\n66\n00:05:51,563 --> 00:05:53,188\nDo you think he''ll pick up the keys?\n\n67\n00:05:53,604 --> 00:05:54,771\nI don''t know\n\n68\n00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:57,438\nI''ve had customers leaving\nkeys here for years\n\n69\n00:05:57,646 --> 00:05:59,188\nSometimes they pick them up in a few days\n\n70\n00:05:59,479 --> 00:06:01,563\nSometimes it takes a few weeks\n\n71\n00:06:02,104 --> 00:06:03,521\nWell, what about most of the time?\n\n72\n00:06:03,771 --> 00:06:06,396\nMost of the time, the keys stay in the jar\n\n73\n00:06:12,854 --> 00:06:14,313\nWell why do you keep them?\n\n74\n00:06:14,771 --> 00:06:15,771\nYou should just throw them out\n\n75\n00:06:15,979 --> 00:06:16,979\nNo\n\n76\n00:06:18,313 --> 00:06:19,813\nNo I couldn''t do that\n\n77\n00:06:21,438 --> 00:06:22,479\nWhy not?\n\n78\n00:06:23,354 --> 00:06:25,063\nIf I threw these keys away\n\n79\n00:06:25,313 --> 00:06:28,063\nthen those doors will be closed forever\n\n80\n00:06:28,354 --> 00:06:29,854\nAnd that shouldn''t be up to me to decide\n\n81\n00:06:31,271 --> 00:06:32,396\nShould it?\n\n82\n00:06:38,021 --> 00:06:39,938\nGuess I''m just looking for a reason\n\n83\n00:06:42,229 --> 00:06:44,646\nWell, from my observations\n\n84\n00:06:45,979 --> 00:06:48,688\nsometimes it''s better off not knowing\n\n85\n00:06:49,021 --> 00:06:52,896\nand other times there''s\nno reason to be found\n\n86\n00:06:52,896 --> 00:06:54,563\nEverything has a reason\n\n87\n00:06:57,604 --> 00:07:00,021\nIt''s like these pies and cakes\n\n88\n00:07:00,771 --> 00:07:02,229\nAt the end of every night\n\n89\n00:07:02,771 --> 00:07:06,313\nthe cheesecake and the apple pie\nare always completely gone\n\n90\n00:07:06,521 --> 00:07:07,854\nThe peach cobbler\n\n91\n00:07:08,146 --> 00:07:10,979\nand the chocolate mousse cake\nare nearly finished\n\n92\n00:07:11,146 --> 00:07:15,979\nBut there''s always a whole blueberry pie\nleft untouched\n\n93\n00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,729\nSo what''s wrong with the blueberry pie?\n\n94\n00:07:19,938 --> 00:07:21,646\nThere''s nothing''s wrong\nwith the blueberry pie\n\n95\n00:07:21,896 --> 00:07:22,938\nIt''s just people make other choices\n\n96\n00:07:23,229 --> 00:07:24,563\nYou can''t blame the blueberry pie\n\n97\n00:07:24,854 --> 00:07:26,563\nIt''s just no one wants it\n\n98\n00:07:28,729 --> 00:07:29,688\nWait!\n\n99\n00:07:31,563 --> 00:07:32,896\nI want a piece\n\n100\n00:07:33,146 --> 00:07:34,188\nWith ice cream?\n\n101\n00:07:37,438 --> 00:07:38,396\nLeave it to me\n\n102\n00:07:45,646 --> 00:07:46,646\nHere we go\n\n103\n00:07:47,521 --> 00:07:48,729\nI hope you enjoy it\n\n104\n00:07:48,938 --> 00:07:49,813\nThanks\n\n105\n00:08:07,688 --> 00:08:08,688\nIt''s not bad\n\n106\n00:08:08,896 --> 00:08:09,813\nReally?\n\n107\n00:08:12,646 --> 00:08:13,729\nYou should try some\n\n108\n00:08:13,938 --> 00:08:16,563\nNo, I''m alright. I have my own\n\n109\n00:09:11,479 --> 00:09:14,104\nWill you tell me the stories\nbehind those other keys?\n\n110\n00:09:16,396 --> 00:09:17,354\nWhat for?\n\n111\n00:09:19,521 --> 00:09:22,188\nI just wondered how they all ended up here\n\n112\n00:09:26,188 --> 00:09:27,146\nPick one\n\n113\n00:09:32,563 --> 00:09:36,313\nThose belonged to a young couple\na few years ago.\n\n114\n00:09:36,521 --> 00:09:37,688\nThey were naive enough to believe\n\n115\n00:09:37,938 --> 00:09:39,813\nthat they were gonna spend the rest\nof their lives together\n\n116\n00:09:41,271 --> 00:09:42,396\nWell, what happened?\n\n117\n00:09:43,188 --> 00:09:44,479\nLife happened\n\n118\n00:09:45,396 --> 00:09:47,146\nThings happened. Yeah, time happened\n\n119\n00:09:48,771 --> 00:09:51,146\nIt''s pretty much always the case more or less\n\n120\n00:09:53,479 --> 00:09:55,688\nOr maybe one of them ran off\nwith someone else\n\n121\n00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:57,771\nMaybe the feelings just went away\n\n122\n00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:05,604\nWhat about these?\n\n123\n00:10:06,021 --> 00:10:08,479\nThose belonged to a little old lady\n\n124\n00:10:08,729 --> 00:10:10,854\nHer best friend would pick them up\nand come to visit her\n\n125\n00:10:11,104 --> 00:10:12,729\nShe dropped them off\nand I never saw her again\n\n126\n00:10:12,979 --> 00:10:14,188\nI presumed, I mean, she was pretty old\n\n127\n00:10:14,396 --> 00:10:16,896\nI presumed she passed away or something\n\n128\n00:10:20,146 --> 00:10:21,563\nWhat about these?\n\n129\n00:10:24,188 --> 00:10:26,813\nThese keys used to belong to a young lad\n\n130\n00:10:27,479 --> 00:10:28,979\nfrom Manchester England\n\n131\n00:10:30,271 --> 00:10:32,271\nwho made plans and had dreams\n\n132\n00:10:32,479 --> 00:10:34,229\nof running every marathon in this country\n\n133\n00:10:34,563 --> 00:10:35,771\nstarting in New York\n\n134\n00:10:37,438 --> 00:10:39,896\nHe was going to write a journal\nabout his experiences\n\n135\n00:10:40,271 --> 00:10:43,104\nand ended up running a cafe.\n\n136\n00:10:44,729 --> 00:10:46,646\nLater they were given to a Russian girl\n\n137\n00:10:48,271 --> 00:10:50,104\nwho loved collecting keys\n\n138\n00:10:51,104 --> 00:10:52,521\nand watching sunsets\n\n139\n00:10:53,604 --> 00:10:57,063\nUnfortunately,\nshe loved sunsets more than the keys\n\n140\n00:10:57,354 --> 00:10:58,896\nand ended up disappearing into one\n\n141\n00:11:01,313 --> 00:11:03,438\nWhy didn''t you go looking for her?\n\n142\n00:11:10,063 --> 00:11:11,104\nWhen I was little\n\n143\n00:11:11,354 --> 00:11:13,604\nme mum used to take me to the park\non weekends\n\n144\n00:11:13,979 --> 00:11:15,813\nShe said if I ever got lost\n\n145\n00:11:16,396 --> 00:11:19,688\nI had to stay in one place\nso that she''d find me\n\n146\n00:11:20,021 --> 00:11:20,938\nDoes that work?\n\n147\n00:11:21,646 --> 00:11:22,854\nNot really\n\n148\n00:11:23,438 --> 00:11:25,479\nShe got lost once looking for me\n\n149\n00:11:26,188 --> 00:11:27,688\nEh, you want some more ice cream?\n\n150\n00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:28,938\nNo thanks\n\n151\n00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:29,938\nYou sure?\n\n152\n00:11:30,188 --> 00:11:31,396\nYeah I''m fine. Thanks\n\n153\n00:12:12,688 --> 00:12:13,729\nYou''re late\n\n154\n00:12:16,354 --> 00:12:17,563\nSame as usual?\n\n155\n00:12:29,688 --> 00:12:30,896\nNo thanks\n\n156\n00:12:37,479 --> 00:12:38,938\nCan I have my keys back?\n\n157\n00:12:39,979 --> 00:12:41,438\nYeah, sure\n\n158\n00:12:45,729 --> 00:12:46,729\nSo...\n\n159\n00:12:48,021 --> 00:12:50,354\nYou two have patched things up then?\n\n160\n00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:53,729\nThanks\n\n161\n00:13:26,229 --> 00:13:27,604\nLousy bloody camera\n\n162\n00:13:32,438 --> 00:13:33,354\nHey!\n\n163\n00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:36,146\nAlright. Come on. Break it-- Alright!\n\n164\n00:13:36,354 --> 00:13:38,188\nTake it outside. Take it out--\n\n165\n00:13:38,438 --> 00:13:38,979\nNone of your business cupcake!\n\n166\n00:13:39,271 --> 00:13:40,063\nDon''t start with me mate!\n\n167\n00:13:40,313 --> 00:13:41,646\nDon''t you start... Come here!\n\n168\n00:13:41,938 --> 00:13:42,813\nRight you come here\n\n169\n00:13:43,229 --> 00:13:44,396\nGet out of my place!\n\n170\n00:13:46,479 --> 00:13:48,146\nDon''t start with me!\n\n171\n00:13:48,210 --> 00:13:49,220\nGet out!\n\n172\n00:13:49,979 --> 00:13:52,063\nHey you haven''t paid yet!\n\n173\n00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:16,521\nWhat happened?\n\n174\n00:14:16,979 --> 00:14:17,854\nDid he hit you?\n\n175\n00:14:18,063 --> 00:14:19,021\nNo!\n\n176\n00:14:19,313 --> 00:14:20,438\nWell what?\n\n177\n00:14:21,771 --> 00:14:23,688\nI got mugged on the subway\n\n178\n00:14:24,188 --> 00:14:26,188\nI thought Pork Chop lived around here?\n\n179\n00:14:27,688 -