issed\n\n209\n00:16:29,313 --> 00:16:31,896\nThat''s going on right in front of me\n\n210\n00:16:34,063 --> 00:16:35,771\nYou must have a lot of tapes\n\n211\n00:16:37,979 --> 00:16:39,604\nI don''t keep them all\n\n212\n00:16:39,813 --> 00:16:41,104\nI''m not that weird\n\n213\n00:16:42,938 --> 00:16:44,396\nOnly the highlights\n\n214\n00:16:56,563 --> 00:16:57,688\nCan I take a look?\n\n215\n00:16:58,896 --> 00:16:59,854\nSure\n\n216\n00:17:01,188 --> 00:17:02,188\nCome around\n\n217\n00:21:14,813 --> 00:21:17,938\nShe left behind her set of keys\nand disappeared that night\n\n218\n00:21:55,813 --> 00:21:59,146\nHow do you say goodbye to someone\nyou can''t imagine living without?\n\n219\n00:22:00,771 --> 00:22:02,271\nI didn''t say goodbye\n\n220\n00:22:06,438 --> 00:22:07,938\nI didn''t say anything\n\n221\n00:22:12,563 --> 00:22:13,896\nI just walked away\n\n222\n00:22:16,563 --> 00:22:17,979\nAt the end of that night\n\n223\n00:22:18,229 --> 00:22:21,021\nI decided to take the longest way\nto cross the street\n\n224\n00:22:30,271 --> 00:22:31,563\nDear Jeremy\n\n225\n00:22:32,521 --> 00:22:34,396\nAs you can see by this postcard\n\n226\n00:22:34,646 --> 00:22:36,104\nI''m now in Memphis, Tennessee\n\n227\n00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:38,865\nHey Lizzy,\nhurry up with those damn pick-ups will ya!\n\n228\n00:22:38,938 --> 00:22:39,438\nComing!\n\n229\n00:22:39,688 --> 00:22:40,188\nCome on hustle it!\n\n230\n00:22:40,521 --> 00:22:42,521\nIt took me a long time to get here\n\n231\n00:22:42,854 --> 00:22:44,938\nAnd I''m not sure how long I''ll be staying\n\n232\n00:22:46,063 --> 00:22:48,646\nDuring the day, I work at a diner downtown\n\n233\n00:22:49,854 --> 00:22:51,563\nI haven''t been able to sleep at night\n\n234\n00:22:51,621 --> 00:22:54,770\nso I''ve also taken a waitressing job at a bar\n\n235\n00:22:56,104 --> 00:23:00,063\nIt''s kind of a dive,\nbut the tips are pretty good\n\n236\n00:23:00,604 --> 00:23:02,729\nWorking two jobs is exhausting\n\n237\n00:23: