n10\n00:02:46,062 --> 00:02:49,649\nHere you go.\nThanks.\n\n11\n00:03:13,423 --> 00:03:17,051\n[Woman Screams]\nYou kids!\n\n12\n00:03:17,177 --> 00:03:20,555\n[ Arguing, Indistinct ]\n\n13\n00:03:23,850 --> 00:03:25,727\n[ Sobbing ]\n\n14\n00:03:27,645 --> 00:03:29,564\nHere.\n[Woman]\nHold it right there!\n\n15\n00:03:29,647 --> 00:03:32,233\n- [Man] What happened?\n- [ Woman ] Step away from her.\n\n16\n00:03:32,358 --> 00:03:34,235\nOh, man,\nhe ain''t done nothing.\n\n17\n00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:36,279\nThose kids.\nWho took your bag?\nThis man?\n\n18\n00:03:36,404 --> 00:03:39,449\nNo, it was a couple of punks.\nThey came and they just ran off.\n\n19\n00:03:39,574 --> 00:03:41,451\nFour-eight, this is Romano.\nRobbery and assault victim...\n\n20\n00:03:41,576 --> 00:03:43,536\nwith facial wound\nat East 42nd entrance.\n\n21\n00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,705\nSir, I''d like you\nto just stand right there.\n\n22\n00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:48,958\nCertainly.\nAre you traveling somewhere?\n\n23\n00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:52,378\nI have arrived.\nMy travels are over\nfor the time being.\n\n24\n00:03:52,462 --> 00:03:55,048\nWhere''s your luggage?\n\n25\n00:03:55,131 --> 00:03:58,927\nI don''t require luggage.\nDo you have a ticket?\n\n26\n00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:00,929\nTrain ticket?\nTicket stub?\n\n27\n00:04:01,012 --> 00:04:03,556\nI didn''t arrive by train.\n\n28\n00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:06,476\nWould you remove your sunglasses\nfor me, please?\n\n29\n00:04:06,601 --> 00:04:11,272\nOh, I''d rather not.\nI''d forgotten,\nbut I mean, wow,\n\n30\n00:04:11,397 --> 00:04:13,441\nYour planet\nis really bright.\n\n31\n00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:16,945\nI see.\nEast 42, we have an E.D.P.\n\n32\n00:04:17,028 --> 00:04:19,072\nI have to ask you\nto come with us, sir.\n\n33\n00:04:19,155 --> 00:04:21,074\nOf course.\n[Handcuffs Lock]\n\n34\n00:04:42,553 --> 00:04:44,681\n[Female Officer]\nFreddy!\n\n35\n00:04:45,932 --> 00:04:48,601\nDid you see this fella\ncome out of a gate?\n\n36\n00:04:48,685 --> 00:04:51,938\nHe didn''t come from no gate.\nBrother came from nowhere.\n\n37\n00:04:52,021 --> 00:04:54,065\nYou know what I''m saying?\n\n38\n00:04:54,148 --> 00:04:56,150\nYeah, Freddy,\nI know what you''re saying.\n\n39\n00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:03,741\n[Car Door Closes]\n\n40\n00:05:05,702 --> 00:05:09,622\n[Car Engine Starts]\n\n41\n00:06:41,923 --> 00:06:44,592\n[Car Door Opens, Closes]\n\n42\n00:06:44,717 --> 00:06:48,763\nI don''t wanna go outside,\nbecause there''s things\nthat can kill you--\n\n43\n00:06:53,726 --> 00:06:55,603\nThank you.\n\n44\n00:06:55,728 --> 00:06:57,730\nIf you breathe\nall those chemicals out there,\n\n45\n00:06:57,855 --> 00:07:00,608\nnot to mention the cosmic rays\nand the West Nile virus,\n\n46\n00:07:00,691 --> 00:07:04,445\nand that other one--\nthe new airborne pigeon disease\nnobody wants to talk about.\n\n47\n00:07:04,570 --> 00:07:06,447\nThe new pigeon disease.\nI''ve heard of that.\n\n48\n00:07:06,531 --> 00:07:09,409\nAnother thing that''s been\nbothering me is the food.\n\n49\n00:07:09,492 --> 00:07:12,495\nThe cafeteria serves\nlukewarm food,\nfull of germs.\n\n50\n00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:14,747\nYou really need to do something\nabout that, Dr. Powel l.\n\n51\n00:07:14,831 --> 00:07:16,749\nHeat is the only thing\nthat kills germs. Heat.\n\n52\n00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:20,545\nPoint taken.\nWe''ll look into that\nright away.\n\n53\n00:07:20,628 --> 00:07:25,049\nIn the meantime,\nI want you to start taking\nYour medication again.\n\n54\n00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:27,802\nIt''ll help you sleep.\nAnd you need the sleep, Ernie.\n\n55\n00:07:27,927 --> 00:07:29,846\nSleep is good.\n\n56\n00:07:29,971 --> 00:07:31,931\n[Buzzer Buzzes]\n\n57\n00:07:32,056 --> 00:07:35,768\nIs our time up?\n\n58\n00:07:35,852 --> 00:07:38,187\nOnly for today, Ernie.\n\n59\n00:07:40,565 --> 00:07:43,025\nTwo calls:\nYour wife, bring home\na bottle of wine.\n\n60\n00:07:43,151 --> 00:07:45,027\nYeah.\nAnd Dr. Chakraborty.\n\n61\n00:07:45,153 --> 00:07:47,613\nA transfer from Bellevue\nhe wants you to take a look at.\n\n62\n00:07:47,738 --> 00:07:52,160\nGreat. Who is it this time?\nJesus Christ or Joan of Arc?\n\n63\n00:07:52,285 --> 00:07:54,996\nDr. Chakraborty didn''t say.\n\n64\n00:08:21,522 --> 00:08:23,608\n[Man]\nHe arrived at Bellevue\na month ago,\n\n65\n00:08:23,691 --> 00:08:26,152\nsuspicion of\nhallucinogenic intoxication.\n\n66\n00:08:26,235 --> 00:08:29,489\nBut, uh, he was found\nnegative for substances\nof any kind.\n\n67\n00:08:29,572 --> 00:08:31,866\nHis EKG, his blood value\nare all normal.\n\n68\n00:08:31,949 --> 00:08:34,243\nThere''s no sign of concussion,\nno brain tumor,\n\n69\n00:08:34,368 --> 00:08:38,080\nno temporal lobe, epilepsy,\nno indication of organic\nabnormality whatsoever.\n\n70\n00:08:38,206 --> 00:08:40,625\nHowever, after one month,\n\n71\n00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:43,544\nhis amnesia and his delusion\nhave persisted.\n\n72\n00:08:44,712 --> 00:08:47,048\nHe claims to be not human.\n\n73\n00:08:47,173 --> 00:08:49,592\nA visitor\nfrom another planet.\n\n74\n00:08:49,717 --> 00:08:52,470\nThey administered Thorazine\non this guy for three weeks...\n\n75\n00:08:52,553 --> 00:08:56,265\nat 300 milligrams a day,\nand he was unresponsive?\n\n76\n00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:59,769\nHow can you be unresponsive\nto 300 milligrams of Thorazine?\nIt''s impossible.\n\n77\n00:08:59,894 --> 00:09:01,854\nThat''s why\nthey sent him to you.\n\n78\n00:09:01,979 --> 00:09:04,440\n[ Sighs ]\nTerrific.\n\n79\n00:09:04,565 --> 00:09:07,902\nNo I.D.,\nno missing persons report\nmatching his description.\n\n80\n00:09:07,985 --> 00:09:10,363\nWhat''s this?\n\n81\n00:09:10,446 --> 00:09:13,282\nHe had it on him.\n\n82\n00:09:15,535 --> 00:09:19,038\nWell, let''s hope\nextraterrestrials\nqualify for Medicaid.\n\n83\n00:09:20,373 --> 00:09:22,375\n[ Secretary ]\nHe''s here, Doctor.\n\n84\n00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:25,086\nThank you, Joyce.\n\n85\n00:09:25,211 --> 00:09:29,924\nMedical record 2-8-7.\nCalls himself Prot.\n\n86\n00:09:30,007 --> 00:09:32,051\n[Knock At Door,\nDoor Opens]\n\n87\n00:09:33,594 --> 00:09:35,930\nThis one''s as gentle\nas a pussycat, Doc.\n\n88\n00:09:36,055 --> 00:09:38,558\nCome in.\nHave a seat.\n\n89\n00:09:38,683 --> 00:09:42,770\n"Have a seat."\nCurious expression.\n\n90\n00:09:44,647 --> 00:09:47,108\nWell, let me introduce\nmyself. I''m--\n\n91\n00:09:47,191 --> 00:09:49,735\nDr. Mark Powell,\nChief of Clinical Psychiatry...\n\n92\n00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:52,321\nof the Manhattan\nPsychiatric Institute.\n\n93\n00:09:52,446 --> 00:09:55,241\nGood. You know\nwhere you are.\n\n94\n00:09:56,701 --> 00:10:00,705\nWell, now, uh...\nProt, is it?\n\n95\n00:10:00,788 --> 00:10:04,083\n"Prote."\nI see, "Prote."\n\n96\n00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:07,128\nWell, Prot,\nwe''re here to--\nMay I?\n\n97\n00:10:08,504 --> 00:10:10,590\nPlease.\n\n98\n00:10:13,259 --> 00:10:16,262\nRed delicious.\nYou call this variety.\n\n99\n00:10:17,388 --> 00:10:19,807\nIt''s my favorite.\n\n100\n00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:23,185\nI''d like to begin\nby asking you...\n\n101\n00:10:23,311 --> 00:10:25,813\nif you know\nwhy you''re here.\n\n102\n00:10:25,938 --> 00:10:29,191\nOf course.\nYou think I''m crazy.\n\n103\n00:10:31,402 --> 00:10:35,948\nWe prefer the term "ill.''''\nDo you think you are ill?\n\n104\n00:10:36,073 --> 00:10:38,326\nA little homesick, perhaps.\n\n105\n00:10:38,451 --> 00:10:41,037\nReally.\nWhere is home?\n\n106\n00:10:41,162 --> 00:10:43,289\nK-PAX.\n\n107\n00:10:43,414 --> 00:10:45,333\nK-PAX?\n\n108\n00:10:45,416 --> 00:10:47,710\nCapital "K,'''' hyphen,\ncapitals "P-A-X.''''\n\n109\n00:10:47,835 --> 00:10:50,212\nK-PAX is a planet.\n\n110\n00:10:50,338 --> 00:10:53,799\nBut don''t worry,\nI''m not going to\nleap out of your chest.\n\n111\n00:10:53,924 --> 00:10:56,802\nI''m not worried.\n\n112\n00:10:56,886 --> 00:10:59,305\nIt’s just that I''m only\nfamiliar with nine planets.\n\n113\n00:10:59,388 --> 00:11:01,766\nWell, actually, there are ten,\nbut that doesn''t matter.\n\n114\n00:11:01,849 --> 00:11:03,976\nI''m not from\nYour solar system.\n\n115\n00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:07,355\nK-PAX is about 1 ,000\nof your light-years\naway from here...\n\n116\n00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:10,191\nin what you would call\nYour constellation Lyra.\n\n117\n00:11:10,316 --> 00:11:12,526\nThat''s quite a ways.\n\n118\n00:11:12,652 --> 00:11:14,654\nI''m curious.\nHow did you get to Earth?\n\n119\n00:11:17,573 --> 00:11:20,993\nIt''s a matter of harnessing\nthe energy of light.\n\n120\n00:11:21,077 --> 00:11:23,621\nI know that sounds\ncrazy to you.\n\n121\n00:11:23,704 --> 00:11:26,791\nYou beings are eons away\nfrom discovering light travel.\n\n122\n00:11:28,751 --> 00:11:30,753\nYou travel\nat the speed of light?\n\n123\n00:11:30,878 --> 00:11:36,008\nOh, no. We can travel\nmany times that speed.\nVarious multiples of "C.''''\n\n124\n00:11:36,092 --> 00:11:40,262\nOtherwise, the trip here\nwould have taken about\n1 ,000 years now, wouldn''t it?\n\n125\n00:11:43,224 --> 00:11:45,935\nWhat if, um,\nI were to tell you...\n\n126\n00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:48,896\nthat according to a man\nwho lived on our planet\nnamed Einstein,\n\n127\n00:11:48,979 --> 00:11:53,901\nthat nothing can travel\nfaster than the speed\nof light?\n\n128\n00:11:54,026 --> 00:11:57,238\nI would say that you misread\nEinstein, Dr. Powell.\nMay I call you Mark?\n\n129\n00:11:57,321 --> 00:12:00,408\nYou see, Mark,\nwhat Einstein actually said...\n\n130\n00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:02,785\nwas that nothing can accelerate\nto the speed of light,\n\n131\n00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:04,870\nbecause its mass\nwould become infinite.\n\n132\n00:12:04,995 --> 00:12:08,999\nEinstein said nothing about\nentities already traveling\nat the speed of light or faster,\n\n133\n00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:12,294\n- at tachyon speeds.\n- Tachyon?\n\n134\n00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:16,048\nI detect a note\nof skepticism, Dr. Powell.\n\n135\n00:12:16,173 --> 00:12:18,592\nOh, not at all