r. Powell ]\nSo that makes you how old?\n\n212\n00:16:58,372 --> 00:17:01,333\n[ Prot ]\nIn Earth terms, 337 years old.\n\n213\n00:17:01,417 --> 00:17:05,713\nI aged about seven getting here,\ntraveling at six multiples\nof "C."\n\n214\n00:17:05,796 --> 00:17:08,716\nBut really, Marko,\nit only seemed like an instant.\n\n215\n00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:13,512\nMarko?\n[ Prot ] Time may warp\nat super light speed.\n\n216\n00:17:13,595 --> 00:17:16,807\nI''d say\naccess one psychosis NOS.\n\n217\n00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:20,728\nThat''s glib to\ncall him a psychotic.\nThat''s a wastebasket diagnosis.\n\n218\n00:17:20,853 --> 00:17:24,148\nOh, yeah?\nHe believes he traveled\nhere from another planet.\n\n219\n00:17:24,231 --> 00:17:26,358\nWhat''s your diagnosis,\njet lag?\n\n220\n00:17:26,442 --> 00:17:28,902\nWell, how come he didn''t\nrespond to the Haldol?\n\n221\n00:17:29,028 --> 00:17:30,904\n[Woman]\nHaldol can make you\nmore psychotic.\n\n222\n00:17:31,030 --> 00:17:33,282\nIt''s rare,\nbut it does happen.\n\n223\n00:17:33,407 --> 00:17:37,828\nLook. I''m not saying\nthat medication can''t be\na useful tool...\n\n224\n00:17:37,911 --> 00:17:40,289\nto help somebody like this,\nbut you can''t--\n\n225\n00:17:40,414 --> 00:17:44,251\nHe maybe a good subject\nfor the "Betazine" protocol.\nThe drug''s on clinical trial.\n\n226\n00:17:44,334 --> 00:17:47,046\nYou want to experiment on him\nbefore we have a diagnosis?\n\n227\n00:17:47,129 --> 00:17:49,381\nDo you have some other idea?\n\n228\n00:17:49,465 --> 00:17:53,427\nHe''s not a danger to anyone.\nHow about getting\nto know him first?\n\n229\n00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:57,222\nIn the meantime,\nwe have ten new transfers\nto take care of.\n\n230\n00:17:57,306 --> 00:18:00,392\n[Dr. Powel l]\nYou know, maybe what''s\nwrong with him...\n\n231\n00:18:00,476 --> 00:18:03,604\nis that he is.\nIs what?\n\n232\n00:18:03,729 --> 00:18:05,898\nFrom the planet K-PAX.\n\n233\n00:18:06,023 --> 00:18:08,233\n[Laughter]\n\n234\n00:18:10,027 --> 00:18:14,323\n[ Woman, Indistinct ]\n\n235\n00:18:16,742 --> 00:18:18,619\n[ Sniffs ]\n\n236\n00:18:43,185 --> 00:18:45,104\nMmm.\n\n237\n00:18:49,566 --> 00:18:52,152\nYour produce alone\nhas been worth the trip.\n\n238\n00:18:57,241 --> 00:19:00,661\n[Dr. Powel l]\nCould you tell me...\n\n239\n00:19:00,744 --> 00:19:03,956\na bit about your boyhood\non K-PAX?\n\n240\n00:19:04,039 --> 00:19:05,958\nWhere were you born?\n\n241\n00:19:07,042 --> 00:19:11,088\nYou were, uh,\nborn, right?\n\n242\n00:19:11,171 --> 00:19:13,090\nK-PAXians have babies?\n\n243\n00:19:13,173 --> 00:19:15,717\nOh, yes, much like on Earth,\nbut unlike you humans,\n\n244\n00:19:15,843 --> 00:19:19,471\nthe reproductive process\nis quite unpleasant for us.\n\n245\n00:19:19,596 --> 00:19:21,932\nCould you compare\nthe effect to something\nthat I might understand?\n\n246\n00:19:22,015 --> 00:19:25,018\nLike a toothache?\nIt''s more like having\nyour nuts in a vlse,\n\n247\n00:19:25,102 --> 00:19:27,020\nexcept we feel it all over.\n\n248\n00:19:27,104 --> 00:19:29,523\nAnd to make matters worse,\nthe sensation is associated...\n\n249\n00:19:29,648 --> 00:19:33,152\nwith something like your nausea,\naccompanied by a very bad smell.\n\n250\n00:19:33,235 --> 00:19:36,488\nThe moment of climax is like\nbeing kicked in the stomach,\n\n251\n00:19:36,572 --> 00:19:39,575\nand then falling into a pool\nof mod droppings.\n\n252\n00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:41,535\nMod droppings?\n\n253\n00:19:41,618 --> 00:19:46,373\nA mod is a being,\nmuch like your skunk,\nonly far more potent.\n\n254\n00:19:48,792 --> 00:19:52,462\nUh, if it''s such\na terrible experience,\n\n255\n00:19:52,546 --> 00:19:56,758\nuh, how do you reproduce?\n\n256\n00:19:56,884 --> 00:19:59,511\nAs carefully as possible.\n\n257\n00:19:59,636 --> 00:20:01,555\nWhat are you doing?\n\n258\n00:20:01,638 --> 00:20:05,475\nWell, you just reminded me\nof something I want to\ninclude in my report.\n\n259\n00:20:05,559 --> 00:20:07,686\nYour report.\nYes, it''s our custom...\n\n260\n00:20:07,769 --> 00:20:10,564\nto compile descriptions\nof the various places\nand people we encounter...\n\n261\n00:20:10,689 --> 00:20:12,608\nthroughout the galaxy.\n\n262\n00:20:17,237 --> 00:20:20,199\nMorning, Betty.\nGood morning, Prot.\n\n263\n00:20:20,282 --> 00:20:22,451\nMorning, Navarro.\nHey, what''s up, man?\n\n264\n00:20:22,576 --> 00:20:25,120\nMr. Friedman.\nMorning, Maria.\n\n265\n00:20:25,245 --> 00:20:29,541\n- I''m Vanessa.\n- [ Navarro ] Just chill.\n\n266\n00:20:31,293 --> 00:20:33,754\nMorning, Bess.\n\n267\n00:20:33,879 --> 00:20:39,051\nShe doesn''t talk to anybody.\nAfraid smoke will come out of\nher mouth when she talks.\n\n268\n00:20:39,134 --> 00:20:41,970\nBeen here since\nshe was a little girl.\nBurned her house down.\n\n269\n00:20:42,095 --> 00:20:45,098\nShouldn''t play with matches.\nVery dangerous.\n\n270\n00:20:45,224 --> 00:20:49,603\nIt was an electrical flare.\nWhy do you make up stories\nlike that?\n\n271\n00:20:49,728 --> 00:20:52,105\nErnie has a very powerful\nimagination.\n\n272\n00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:57,653\n[Woman]\nPhil listen!\n\n273\n00:20:57,778 --> 00:21:02,658\nCome on, Doris.\nYou gotta come out of\nYour room sometime.\n\n274\n00:21:02,783 --> 00:21:04,785\nLook what I brought\njust for you.\n\n275\n00:21:06,328 --> 00:21:08,997\n[Doris]\nPooh, pooh, pooh, pooh,\npooh, pooh, pooh, pooh.\n\n276\n00:21:09,122 --> 00:21:11,416\n[Intern]\nDo that again,\nyou go up to three.\n\n277\n00:21:13,335 --> 00:21:17,089\nHer Royal Highness never,\never comes out of her room.\nNot even to eat.\n\n278\n00:21:17,172 --> 00:21:19,341\nNo wonder she''s here.\nI''m sick and tired\nof this shit.\n\n279\n00:21:19,466 --> 00:21:22,427\nEveryday, coming up here\nand shooting food at me.\nI hate this.\n\n280\n00:21:28,850 --> 00:21:31,103\n[Clanging]\n\n281\n00:21:31,186 --> 00:21:33,981\nThe service here\nis atrocious!\n\n282\n00:21:35,107 --> 00:21:39,319\nGood morning, Mrs. Archer.\nDoris.\n\n283\n00:21:39,403 --> 00:21:41,655\n[ Chuckles ]\n\n284\n00:21:41,738 --> 00:21:45,117\nI wasn''t expecting\nany gentleman callers...\n\n285\n00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,452\nuntil this afternoon.\n\n286\n00:21:47,536 --> 00:21:49,454\nExcuse me.\n\n287\n00:22:03,218 --> 00:22:05,220\nYou have a place\nset for two.\n\n288\n00:22:07,723 --> 00:22:12,644\nOh, yes. Um...\nI''m expecting someone.\n\n289\n00:22:12,728 --> 00:22:14,730\nHow long\nhave you been waiting?\n\n290\n00:22:14,855 --> 00:22:16,815\nEleven years.\n\n291\n00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:19,484\n[ Laughs ]\n\n292\n00:22:19,609 --> 00:22:24,031\nFor some around here\nmight...\n\n293\n00:22:24,114 --> 00:22:27,200\ncall that crazy,\nbut I prefer to call it...\n\n294\n00:22:27,326 --> 00:22:29,703\n[ Sniffles ]\nromantic.\n\n295\n00:22:29,828 --> 00:22:32,831\nRomantic.\nLike a, uh...\n\n296\n00:22:34,166 --> 00:22:36,835\nwaltz in the moonlight,\nor a...\n\n297\n00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:39,671\ncandlelit dinner...\n\n298\n00:22:39,796 --> 00:22:42,174\nor a sunset.\nOh, we have those.\n\n299\n00:22:42,257 --> 00:22:45,052\nOn K-PAX, we have two suns.\n\n300\n00:22:45,177 --> 00:22:49,181\nThey rlse together\nonly once every 200 years.\n\n301\n00:22:49,264 --> 00:22:51,266\nAnd that is quite a sight.\n\n302\n00:22:54,603 --> 00:22:57,397\nHe most definitely\nhas a sensitivity\nto white light,\n\n303\n00:22:57,481 --> 00:23:01,485\nbut I think\nit''s his range that\nYou''ll find interesting.\n\n304\n00:23:01,568 --> 00:23:03,403\nWhat am I looking at?\n\n305\n00:23:03,528 --> 00:23:07,574\nHe can detect light\nat a wavelength of up to\n300 to 400 angstroms.\n\n306\n00:23:08,825 --> 00:23:11,036\nUltraviolet.\n\n307\n00:23:11,161 --> 00:23:14,039\nOf course,\nProt''s explanation is that...\n\n308\n00:23:14,122 --> 00:23:18,502\ndue to his planet''s\npeculiar quality of light\ncaused by its two suns,\n\n309\n00:23:18,585 --> 00:23:24,049\nK-PAXians are used to\nlight conditions much like\nour twilight most of the time