e.\n\n409\n00:29:57,317 --> 00:29:59,194\nSomeone change\nhis medication?\n\n410\n00:29:59,319 --> 00:30:03,156\nI gave him his usual,\nAnafronil, 250 milligrams.\n\n411\n00:30:07,744 --> 00:30:10,705\n[Dr. Powel l]\nHmm. Well, something''s\nwrong with him.\n\n412\n00:30:10,830 --> 00:30:15,794\nAn obsessive-compulsive\ndoesn''t just sit there\nlooking out the window.\n\n413\n00:30:24,260 --> 00:30:26,179\nHowie?\n\n414\n00:30:31,100 --> 00:30:33,520\nGood morning,\nDr. Powell.\n\n415\n00:30:33,645 --> 00:30:38,024\nGood morning.\nBut are you looking\nfor something?\n\n416\n00:30:38,107 --> 00:30:40,026\nBluebird.\n\n417\n00:30:40,109 --> 00:30:42,153\nThe bluebird?\n\n418\n00:30:42,278 --> 00:30:44,197\nThe bluebird of happiness.\n\n419\n00:30:46,699 --> 00:30:49,661\nProt told me to find\nthe bluebird of happiness.\n\n420\n00:30:49,744 --> 00:30:52,413\nProt told you.\n\n421\n00:30:52,539 --> 00:30:54,415\nIt''s a task.\n\n422\n00:30:54,541 --> 00:30:56,417\nThe first of three.\n\n423\n00:30:58,378 --> 00:31:01,214\nI don''t know what\nthe other two are yet.\n\n424\n00:31:01,339 --> 00:31:04,008\nHe''ll tell me.\n\n425\n00:31:04,092 --> 00:31:08,096\nIf I complete all three,\n\n426\n00:31:08,221 --> 00:31:10,098\nI''ll be cured.\n\n427\n00:31:22,068 --> 00:31:25,029\n[Prot] There.\nMaintain your breathing.\n\n428\n00:31:25,154 --> 00:31:27,574\nThat''s it.\nNow you see?\n\n429\n00:31:27,699 --> 00:31:30,118\nThere are none of\nthese ammonia particles\nthat you''re so worried about.\n\n430\n00:31:30,243 --> 00:31:33,246\nIn the first place,\nI would be able to see them.\nGood morning, Sal.\n\n431\n00:31:33,371 --> 00:31:35,248\nAnd I don''t.\n[Sal]\nGood morning, Dr. Stinky.\n\n432\n00:31:35,373 --> 00:31:37,876\nRinged monkey, 7:00.\n\n433\n00:31:42,422 --> 00:31:44,299\nTake a bath.\nTake a bath.\n\n434\n00:31:44,424 --> 00:31:47,886\nErnie, could you excuse us\nfor a moment, please?\nMm-hmm.\n\n435\n00:31:48,011 --> 00:31:49,929\nGood to, uh,\nsee you outside, Ernie.\n\n436\n00:31:50,013 --> 00:31:53,224\nThank you.\nOh, Ernie, you stink.\n\n437\n00:31:53,308 --> 00:31:56,603\nProt, it''s one thing\nto take an interest\nin your fellow patients.\n\n438\n00:31:56,728 --> 00:31:59,731\nIt''s quite another\nto make them think\nthat you can cure them.\n\n439\n00:31:59,814 --> 00:32:01,774\nYou seem overly upset,\nMark.\n\n440\n00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:05,403\nTo borrow a phrase from Navarro,\nYou need to chill.\n\n441\n00:32:05,528 --> 00:32:08,781\nFor your information,\nall beings have the capacity\nto cure themselves, Mark.\n\n442\n00:32:08,823 --> 00:32:11,534\nThis is something\nwe''ve known on K-PAX\nfor millions of years.\n\n443\n00:32:11,618 --> 00:32:15,747\nListen to me.\nOn this planet,\nI''m a doctor, you''re a patient.\n\n444\n00:32:15,872 --> 00:32:19,667\nDoctor. Patient.\nCurious human distinction.\n\n445\n00:32:19,792 --> 00:32:22,712\nIt''s not your job\nto cure Howie.\n\n446\n00:32:22,795 --> 00:32:25,798\nOr Ernie or Maria\nor anyone else.\nIt''s mine.\n\n447\n00:32:25,882 --> 00:32:27,967\nThen why haven''t\nYou cured them yet?\n\n448\n00:32:30,136 --> 00:32:34,682\nOh, by the way,\nhere are the answers\nto the questions you asked me.\n\n449\n00:32:37,602 --> 00:32:39,479\nI hope they meet\nYour satisfaction.\n\n450\n00:32:54,202 --> 00:32:56,120\n[Russell ]\nI don''t know what to say, Mark.\n\n451\n00:32:56,204 --> 00:32:59,916\nI mean, this is--\nthis is pretty wild stuff.\n\n452\n00:32:59,999 --> 00:33:04,003\nGibberish, huh?\nWell, not exactly.\n\n453\n00:33:04,128 --> 00:33:06,381\nI mean, see,\n\n454\n00:33:06,506 --> 00:33:09,342\nYour patient indicates\nhis planet, K-PAX,\n\n455\n00:33:09,467 --> 00:33:13,471\norbitingan eclipsing\nbinary star system--\nAgape and Satori.\n\n456\n00:33:13,554 --> 00:33:16,307\nYeah.\nNear the Constellation Lyra.\n\n457\n00:33:16,432 --> 00:33:18,518\nHe could have\nlooked that up, right?\n\n458\n00:33:19,686 --> 00:33:22,689\nThat''s the funny thing, Mark.\nNot really.\n\n459\n00:33:22,814 --> 00:33:26,693\nI mean, except for my boss,\nDuncan Flynn,\n\n460\n00:33:26,776 --> 00:33:29,654\none of the foremost\nastrophysicists in the world...\n\n461\n00:33:29,737 --> 00:33:34,075\nand maybe two or three\nof his colleagues,\n\n462\n00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:37,453\nnobody knows much about\nthe possibility of planets\nin this star system yet.\n\n463\n00:33:37,537 --> 00:33:39,998\nIt hasn''t even been reported\nin any journals.\n\n464\n00:33:41,249 --> 00:33:43,876\nTell me, honestly,\n\n465\n00:33:44,002 --> 00:33:46,004\ndid Duncan put you\nup to this?\n\n466\n00:33:46,087 --> 00:33:48,715\nYou know--\nYou know, like a joke?\n\n467\n00:33:48,881 --> 00:33:52,510\n[ Chuckles ]\nNo. It''s no joke, Steve.\n\n468\n00:33:52,635 --> 00:33:54,846\nUh, tell me,\n\n469\n00:33:54,971 --> 00:33:58,224\ndo you know of any missing\nastrophysicists?\n\n470\n00:33:58,349 --> 00:34:01,811\n[ Laughs ]\nCan''t say I do.\n[ Chuckles ]\n\n471\n00:34:01,894 --> 00:34:05,523\nBut there''s one or two\naround here who''d sure like\nto meet this fella of yours.\n\n472\n00:34:05,606 --> 00:34:08,109\nThanks a lot, Steve.\nI sure appreciate it.\n\n473\n00:34:08,151 --> 00:34:14,657\n[Rachel]\n\n474\n00:34:14,657 --> 00:34:16,951\n[ Prot On Tape ]\nBut unlike you humans,\nthe reproductive process...\n\n475\n00:34:17,076 --> 00:34:18,995\nis an unpleasant one for us.\n[Rachel]\nStart again.\n\n476\n00:34:19,037 --> 00:34:22,832\n[ Dr. Powell''s Voice ]\nWhat way is it unpleasant?\n\n477\n00:34:22,832 --> 00:34:24,751\n[ Prot On Tape ]\nIt''s a pain--\n\n478\n00:34:24,834 --> 00:34:26,753\n[ Tape Recorder Off ]\n\n479\n00:34:26,836 --> 00:34:29,255\n{#####[Piano Continues,\n"''Mary Had A Little Lamb''"]\n\n480\n00:34:34,385 --> 00:34:38,806\n[ Rachel ]\nGood. Not too fast.\nOkay.\n\n481\n00:34:46,355 --> 00:34:48,274\n{#####[Piano Continues]\n\n482\n00:34:51,611 --> 00:34:53,488\n[ Sighs ]\n\n483\n00:34:53,613 --> 00:34:55,531\n{#####[Continues]\n\n484\n00:36:48,603 --> 00:36:50,813\nSo, this is\nYour neighborhood, huh?\n\n485\n00:36:56,736 --> 00:36:59,697\n[ Chattering ]\n\n486\n00:36:59,780 --> 00:37:02,783\nHello, gentlemen.\nSure appreciate you\nmeeting with us.\n\n487\n00:37:02,909 --> 00:37:06,078\nThank you, Dr. Powell.\nWe''d like to get to the bottom\nof this just as much as you.\n\n488\n00:37:06,204 --> 00:37:10,291\nThank you, Doctor.\nGreat. Let me introduce\nYou to Prot.\n\n489\n00:37:12,418 --> 00:37:15,421\nIt''s a pleasure\nto meet you, Prot.\nI''m Dr. Becker.\n\n490\n00:37:15,504 --> 00:37:18,049\nThis is Dr. Flynn.\n\n491\n00:37:18,132 --> 00:37:20,593\nDrs. Patel and Hessler.\n\n492\n00:37:22,345 --> 00:37:26,891\nDoctor. Doctor.\nDoctor. Doctor.\n\n493\n00:37:28,267 --> 00:37:30,478\nHow many doctors\nare there on this planet?\n\n494\n00:37:30,603 --> 00:37:32,438\n[ Laughs ]\n\n495\n00:37:47,620 --> 00:37:51,165\nHere, Prot.\nHave a seat.\n\n496\n00:37:51,290 --> 00:37:54,418\n"Have a seat.''''\nOh, shit!\n\n497\n00:37:56,712 --> 00:37:58,923\nFeel at home?\n\n498\n00:38:04,095 --> 00:38:05,972\nWe found your notes\nquite interesting, Prot,\n\n499\n00:38:06,097 --> 00:38:09,225\nand we''d like to ask you\nsome questions,\nif that''s all right.\n\n500\n00:38:09,308 --> 00:38:12,478\nBe my guest.\nGood.\nThen I’ll jump right in.\n\n501\n00:38:12,603 --> 00:38:14,855\nMake sure you can swim.\n\n502\n00:38:14,981 --> 00:38:17,316\n[ Chuckles ]\nYes, well,\n\n503\n00:38:17,441 --> 00:38:20,945\nlet''s start with this idea\nof light travel, shall we?\n\n504\n00:38:22,571 --> 00:38:24,615\nWhat can you tell us\nabout that?\n\n505\n00:38:26,617 --> 00:38:28,494\nAbsolutely nothing.\n\n506\n00:38:28,661 --> 00:38:31,080\nIf I told you,\nyou''d blow yourselves up.\n\n507\n00:38:31,163 --> 00:38:33,124\nOr worse,\nsomeone else.\n\n508\n00:38:33,207 --> 00:38:36,294\nYou''d be surprised\nhow much energy\nis in a beam of light.\n\n509\n00:38:36,377 --> 00:38:39,463\nHmm. Well, then,\n\n510\n00:38:39,588 --> 00:38:44,