1393\n01:49:01,640 --> 01:49:03,558\nRepeat:\nHe''s moving!\n\n1394\n01:49:03,600 --> 01:49:05,560\nWhat the hell?\n\n1395\n01:49:21,284 --> 01:49:23,828\nWait for me, you--\n\n1396\n01:49:30,043 --> 01:49:31,962\n[ Grunts ]\n\n1397\n01:49:41,304 --> 01:49:43,848\nSon of a bitch.\n\n1398\n01:49:51,982 --> 01:49:53,900\nOh, God.\n\n1399\n01:49:57,362 --> 01:50:00,031\nOh, man.\nOh, God.\n\n1400\n01:50:00,115 --> 01:50:03,994\nCall a code blue.\nHelp me.\nLet''s get him.\n\n1401\n01:50:14,838 --> 01:50:17,841\n[ Monitor Beeping ]\n\n1402\n01:50:19,301 --> 01:50:22,304\nWho''s that?\nBeats me.\nHow''d he get in here?\n\n1403\n01:50:22,429 --> 01:50:26,308\nThat''s not Prot.\nHe''s definitely\nnot Prot.\n\n1404\n01:50:26,391 --> 01:50:29,519\nCertainly not.\nProt''s gone.\n\n1405\n01:50:32,939 --> 01:50:34,858\nWhere''s Bess?\n\n1406\n01:50:34,941 --> 01:50:38,153\n[Man]\nWhere''s Bess? Bess?\n\n1407\n01:50:50,540 --> 01:50:53,001\nHe chose Bess.\n\n1408\n01:50:53,084 --> 01:50:55,003\nBitch!\n\n1409\n01:50:55,128 --> 01:50:57,589\n[Man]\nGood-bye, Bess.\n\n1410\n01:50:59,299 --> 01:51:02,093\nGood for you,\nhomegirl.\n\n1411\n01:51:20,403 --> 01:51:23,531\nBess went to K-PAX.\n\n1412\n01:51:45,970 --> 01:51:49,349\n[ Mark''s Voice ]\nPatient 287, Robert Porter.\n\n1413\n01:51:50,809 --> 01:51:54,104\nHow I wish I could say that\nRobert sat up one fine day...\n\n1414\n01:51:54,270 --> 01:51:56,981\nand said, "''I''m hungry.\nGot any fruit?''"\n\n1415\n01:51:58,942 --> 01:52:01,403\nLike most catatonics,\n\n1416\n01:52:01,528 --> 01:52:03,405\nhe probably hears\nevery word we say...\n\n1417\n01:52:03,530 --> 01:52:06,741\nbut refuses\nor is unable to respond.\n\n1418\n01:52:08,201 --> 01:52:12,330\nNevertheless,\nI keep him up to date.\n\n1419\n01:52:15,125 --> 01:52:17,252\nLet''s see.\nI told you about Howie.\n\n1420\n01:52:17,377 --> 01:52:19,754\nHe got that job\nat the public library.\n\n1421\n01:52:21,131 --> 01:52:25,051\nAnd Ernie, he''s determined\nto be a crisis counselor.\n\n1422\n01:52:25,135 --> 01:52:29,264\nThe only one we''re, uh,\nreally concerned about is Bess.\n\n1423\n01:52:29,431 --> 01:52:31,933\nYou know, we''ve checked\nhalfway houses, shelters,\n\n1424\n01:52:32,058 --> 01:52:34,728\nchurches, bus stops.\n\n1425\n01:52:35,937 --> 01:52:38,481\nNothing.\n\n1426\n01:52:38,523 --> 01:52:41,151\nUh, we don''t understand.\nIt''s like...\n\n1427\n01:52:41,192 --> 01:52:44,154\npeople don''t just disappear.\n\n1428\n01:52:47,907 --> 01:52:50,243\nJuly 27th ?\n\n1429\n01:52:50,368 --> 01:52:53,580\nYou wouldn''t happen to know\nanything about that, would you?\n\n1430\n01:52:55,874 --> 01:52:57,792\nRobert?\n\n1431\n01:53:02,630 --> 01:53:05,049\nNo.\n\n1432\n01:53:05,091 --> 01:53:07,510\nWell, maybe\nit''ll come to you.\n\n1433\n01:53:09,971 --> 01:53:12,390\nWhenever you''re ready,\nI''ll be waiting.\n\n1434\n01:53:39,501 --> 01:53:42,212\n[Prot''s Voice]\nI want to tell you\nsomething, Mark,\n\n1435\n01:53:42,378 --> 01:53:44,380\nsomething you\ndo not yet know,\n\n1436\n01:53:44,464 --> 01:53:47,842\nbut we K-PAXians have been\naround long enough\nto have discovered.\n\n1437\n01:53:49,344 --> 01:53:51,513\nThe universe will expand,\n\n1438\n01:53:51,679 --> 01:53:53,681\nthen it will collapse\nback on itself,\n\n1439\n01:53:53,848 --> 01:53:56,267\nand then it will\nexpand again.\n\n1440\n01:53:56,351 --> 01:53:59,562\nIt will repeat\nthis process forever.\n\n1441\n01:53:59,687 --> 01:54:02,690\nWhat you don''t know is that\nwhen the universe expands again,\n\n1442\n01:54:02,774 --> 01:54:06,027\neverything will be\nas it is now.\n\n1443\n01:54:06,110 --> 01:54:10,323\nWhat ever mistakes you make\nthis time around, you will\nlive through on your next pass.\n\n1444\n01:54:10,448 --> 01:54:12,909\nEvery mistake you make...\n\n1445\n01:54:12,951 --> 01:54:14,911\nyou will live through...\n\n1446\n01:54:14,953 --> 01:54:18,998\nagain and again, forever.\n\n1447\n01:54:19,082 --> 01:54:22,877\nSo my advice to you is to\nget it right this time around,\n\n1448\n01:54:22,961 --> 01:54:25,463\nbecause this time...\n\n1449\n01:54:25,630 --> 01:54:27,924\nis all you have.\n\n1450\n01:54:38,518 --> 01:54:42,230\nYou''re lookin'' great,\nMichael.\nThink so?\n\n1451\n01:54:42,313 --> 01:54:44,649\nThanks.\nHow you doin''?\n\n1452\n01:54:44,691 --> 01:54:47,026\nGood. How was your--\nHow was your trip?\n\n1453\n01:54:47,110 --> 01:54:49,320\nWas it--\nWas it good?\n\n1454\n01:55:35,033 --> 01:55:38,411\n{##Maybe this is forever###\n\n1455\n01:55:38,494 --> 01:55:40,788\n{##Forever fades away###\n\n1456\n01:55:42,248 --> 01:55:44,500\n{##Like a rocket ascending###\n\n1457\n01:55:44,542 --> 01:55:48,087\n{##Into space###\n\n1458\n01:55:49,464 --> 01:55:52,884\n{## Could you not be sad###\n\n1459\n01:55:53,051 --> 01:55:56,054\n{## Could you not breakdown###\n\n1460\n01:55:56,220 --> 01:55:58,723\n{##After all###\n\n1461\n01:55:58,890 --> 01:56:01,309\n{##I won''t let go###\n\n1462\n01:56:01,351 --> 01:56:06,898\n{## Until you''re safe and sound###\n\n1463\n01:56:08,650 --> 01:56:14,030\n{## Until you''re safe and sound###\n\n1464\n01:56:15,740 --> 01:56:19,160\n{## There''s beauty in release###\n\n1465\n01:56:19,243 --> 01:56:22,789\n{## There''s no one left\nto please###\n\n1466\n01:56:22,872 --> 01:56:26,542\n{##But you and me###\n\n1467\n01:56:39,597 --> 01:56:43,017\n{##I don''t blame you\nfor quitting###\n\n1468\n01:56:43,101 --> 01:56:46,688\n{##I know you really tried###\n\n1469\n01:56:46,771 --> 01:56:48,982\n{## Only you could hang on###\n\n1470\n01:56:49,107 --> 01:56:53,736\n{## Through the night###\n\n1471\n01:56:53,820 --> 01:56:57,448\n{## ''Cause I don''t\nwanna be lonely###\n\n1472\n01:56:57,532 --> 01:57:00,451\n{##I don''t wanna be scared###\n\n1473\n01:57:00,493 --> 01:57:03,121\n{##And all our friends###\n\n1474\n01:57:03,287 --> 01:57:05,790\n{##Are waiting there###\n\n1475\n01:57:05,873 --> 01:57:11,671\n{## Until you''re safe and sound###\n\n1476\n01:57:13,131 --> 0